<br>
Soot obtained by burning vegetable (like pine tree) oil is blended with glue juice, shaped in the form of a short stick and dried. You rub the soot stick against an ink stone adding water. Then you can get black ink for calligraphy.<br>
<br>
Thesedays however, many kind of synthetic ink is available and it is of liquid form in a small bottle.<br>
<br>
Just for your information.<br>
